<subSubSection id="C31888CFFFF95633FCFCD6D0FFC600B9" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFF95634FCFCD6D0F92C0062" blockId="27.[837,1468,1728,2016]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF95634FCFCD6D0FFA401A9" bold="true" box="[839,975,1728,1752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Description</emphasis>
(
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFF95634FC58D6D0FF9201A9" box="[995,1017,1728,1752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFF95634FBB2D6D0F87601A9" box="[1033,1053,1728,1752]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Relatively large blackish fly, with sexually dimorphic dark wing markings; agreeing with description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF95634FC5AD6ECF8050062" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[993,1134,1788,1811]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF95634FC5AD6ECF8050062" box="[993,1134,1788,1811]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except as indicated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFF95634FCDED708FF9F0091" blockId="27.[837,1468,1728,2016]" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF95634FCDED708FF890041" box="[869,994,1816,1840]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head: antenna tawny-yellow. Thorax black to brown-black. Wing markings of female resembling those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFF95634FCD9D744FF86001A" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[866,1005,1876,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFF95634FCD9D744FF86001A" box="[866,1005,1876,1899]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except that discal crossvein lies completely within transverse brown band (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFF95634FB2BD760F88B00F9" box="[1168,1248,1904,1928]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
); in male distal dark zone reduced to narrow brown margin on costal section from vein 2 to vein 4 and brown stripe on apical part of vein 4 (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFF95634FC23D7D8FF8C0091" box="[920,999,1992,2016]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="51">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7D8BCCFFFE5633FF77D4D6F9500387" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684920" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4684920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684920/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" startId="28.[204,275,1222,1244]" targetBox="[206,1338,208,1196]" targetPageId="28">
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FF77D4D6F9500387" blockId="28.[204,1339,1221,1270]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
Figures 52, 53. 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FEE2D4D6FDEA03AA" box="[345,385,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">(52)</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FE3CD4D6FEE803AD" authority="(Hennig)" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[391,643,1222,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FE3CD4D6FE4C03AA" box="[391,551,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Bama papuanum</emphasis>
(Hennig)
</taxonomicName>
, distal part of aedeagus. Scale = 0.2 mm. 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FC44D4D6F84D03AA" box="[1023,1062,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">(53)</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FB90D4D6F95E03AD" authority="McAlpine" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" box="[1067,1333,1222,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shinonagai">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FB90D4D6F8A403AA" box="[1067,1231,1222,1243]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Bama shinonagai</emphasis>
McAlpine
</taxonomicName>
, left wing of holotype, male. 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FE68D4F0FD800384" box="[467,491,1248,1269]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">bu</emphasis>
, bulb; 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FD90D4F1FE5C0387" box="[555,567,1249,1270]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">g</emphasis>
, glans; 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FDC4D4F0FEF90384" box="[639,658,1248,1269]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">lg</emphasis>
, distal lobe of glans; 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FCE3D4F1FF1B0387" box="[856,880,1249,1270]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">pg</emphasis>
, lobe of preglans; 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FBA7D4F1F8470387" box="[1052,1068,1249,1270]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">st</emphasis>
, stipe; 
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FBD4D4F0F8170384" box="[1135,1148,1248,1269]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">tf</emphasis>
, terminal filaments.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FF2CD575FE8602A4" blockId="28.[119,749,1381,1992]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FF2CD575FCB3020C" box="[151,216,1381,1405]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Head.</emphasis>
Postfrons near mid-length c. 0.37–0.38 as wide as head; height of cheek 0.23 (male)–0.25 (female) of height of eye. Arista (only intact in female) with slightly longer hairs than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FF42D5AEFDEA02A4" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[249,385,1470,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FF42D5AEFDEA02A4" box="[249,385,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Prelabrum moderately prominent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FF2CD5CBFE1001B1" blockId="28.[119,749,1381,1992]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FF2CD5CBFC870282" box="[151,236,1499,1523]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Thorax.</emphasis>
Central part of mesoscutum apparently without pruinescence between setulae. Mid coxa (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFFE5633FDEDD5E8FEC20161" box="[598,681,1528,1552]" captionStart="Figures 48–51" captionStartId="27.[167,239,1461,1483]" captionTargetBox="[167,1465,151,1450]" captionTargetId="figure-230@27.[167,1467,151,1450]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figures 48–51. Bama papuanum (Hennig). (48) Right wing of female (holotype of X. papuana). (49) Right wing of male (holotype of X. strigata). (50) Humeral region of right wing of female, showing microtrichia on membrane. (51) Mid coxae of male from right side." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684918/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
) with relatively weak marginal comb of mainly yellow setulae, medially bearing moderately prominent lobe with flat anterior surface and single stout terminal setula. Wing: penultimate section of vein 4 less than half as long as anterior crossvein; first and second basal cells with somewhat more extensive microtrichiation than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FE5CD6B9FE1801B1" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[487,627,1705,1728]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FE5CD6B9FE1801B1" box="[487,627,1705,1728]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FF2CD6D5FEC400B9" blockId="28.[119,749,1381,1992]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FF2CD6D5FD6A01AC" box="[151,257,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Female: tergite 3 slightly longer than compound tergite 1+2; sternites not clearly visible. Male: sternite 4 not observed; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="1339C7C1FFFE5633FEEED710FDC80069" box="[341,419,1792,1816]" captionStart="Figures 52, 53" captionStartId="28.[204,275,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[206,1338,208,1196]" captionTargetId="figure-9@28.[204,1338,198,1196]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figures 52, 53.(52) Bama papuanum (Hennig), distal part of aedeagus.Scale = 0.2 mm.(53) BamashinonagaiMcAlpine, left wing of holotype, male.bu, bulb;g, glans;lg, distal lobe of glans;pg, lobe of preglans;st, stipe;tf, terminal filaments." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4684920" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4684920/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) with preglans bearing narrow, acute, leaf-like lobe entirely lacking peg-like spinules; flexible section very short; glans slightly longer than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FFC2D749FD6E0001" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[121,261,1881,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FFC2D749FD6E0001" box="[121,261,1881,1904]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its distal membranous lobe bearing relatively large, rounded sclerite; bulb c. half as long as glans; both terminal filaments much longer than those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FDE1D784FE8D00DA" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[602,742,1940,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FDE1D784FE8D00DA" box="[602,742,1940,1963]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, longer (left) filament only slightly shorter than glans.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FC83D576F95202C9" blockId="28.[794,1422,1381,1464]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FC83D576FFD6020C" box="[824,957,1382,1405]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Dimensions.</emphasis>
Total length, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFFE5633FBE9D576F80D020C" box="[1106,1126,1382,1405]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CFA76A1FFFE5633FBD5D576F8A9020C" box="[1134,1218,1382,1406]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="9.2">9.2 mm</quantity>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFFE5633FB75D576F889020C" box="[1230,1250,1382,1405]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CFA76A1FFFE5633FB52D576F954020C" box="[1257,1343,1382,1406]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.2" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="9.2">9.2 mm</quantity>
; length of thorax, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFFE5633FC3DD593FFF102EB" box="[902,922,1411,1434]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CFA76A1FFFE5633FC1BD593FF9F02EB" box="[928,1012,1411,1435]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFFE5633FC45D593F87902EB" box="[1022,1042,1411,1434]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity id="4CFA76A1FFFE5633FBACD593F80702EB" box="[1047,1132,1411,1435]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
; length of wing, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFFE5633FAA7D593F95B02EB" box="[1308,1328,1411,1434]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
9.0 mm, 
<specimenCount id="9D0410CDFFFE5633FCA1D5B1FF4502C9" box="[794,814,1441,1464]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
10.0 mm; length of glans of aedeagus, 
<quantity id="4CFA76A1FFFE5633FB69D5B0F95E02C9" box="[1234,1333,1440,1464]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="0.48">0.48 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FCA1D5CBF8470023" blockId="28.[792,1423,1499,1992]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FCA1D5CBFF310282" bold="true" box="[794,858,1499,1523]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">Notes</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF93A6B5FFFE5633FCDED5CBF86B0282" author="Hennig, W" box="[869,1024,1499,1523]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" pagination="304 - 318" refId="ref17139" refString="Hennig, W. 1940. Aussereuropaische Psiliden und Platystomiden im Deutschen Entomologischen Institut. Arbeiten uber morphologische und taxonomische Entomologie 7: 304 - 318, pl. 24." type="journal article" year="1940">Hennig (1940)</bibRefCitation>
determined the male and female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FACED5CCFFE00161" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FACED5CCFFE00161" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate species, though with an expression of doubt. After careful comparison of Hennig’s two 
<typeStatus id="54B965E6FFFE5633FADAD606F9E4015F" box="[1377,1423,1558,1582]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
specimens with both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FBC6D624F97E013A" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1149,1301,1588,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FBC6D624F97E013A" box="[1149,1301,1588,1611]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species, I am convinced that the former represent one species, showing sexual dimorphism in wing markings. The slightly stronger curvature of the apical section of vein 
<quantity id="4CFA76A1FFFE5633FAD8D69BF9E701D2" box="[1379,1420,1675,1699]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
the male specimen than in the female is also observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FCA1D6D6FFCC01AC" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[794,935,1734,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FCA1D6D6FFCC01AC" box="[794,935,1734,1757]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in at least some specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FA99D6D6F9ED01AC" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1314,1414,1733,1757]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickeli">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FA99D6D6F9ED01AC" box="[1314,1414,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. bickeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The less extensive dark wing markings of the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FACDD6F4FFE20069" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FACDD6F4FFE20069" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than in the female of the species is a more extreme development of the condition also present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FB41D70EF9ED0044" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[1274,1414,1822,1845]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FB41D70EF9ED0044" box="[1274,1414,1822,1845]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FCA1D72CFF150022" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[794,894,1851,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bickeli">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FCA1D72CFF150022" box="[794,894,1851,1875]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. bickeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FC02D72CF84D0022" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[953,1062,1852,1875]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martini">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FC02D72CF84D0022" box="[953,1062,1852,1875]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. martini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBDDB44FFFE5633FC83D748FFC600B9" blockId="28.[792,1423,1499,1992]" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">
The details of the aedeagus, including the proportions of the parts and especially the nature of the lobe of the preglans leave no doubt as to the distinction of 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FB79D784F93800DA" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2001" baseAuthorityName="Hennig" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1218,1363,1940,1963]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papuanum">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FB79D784F93800DA" box="[1218,1363,1940,1963]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. papuanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C02A0C7FFFE5633FCA7D7A1FFCD00B9" authorityName="McAlpine" authorityYear="2015" box="[796,934,1969,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Platystomatidae" genus="Bama" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monstrans">
<emphasis id="B9760756FFFE5633FCA7D7A1FFCD00B9" box="[796,934,1969,1992]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="52">B. monstrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
